        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  Centralized import surface for all attachment extractors: exposes AbstractAttachmentsExtractor, all Office-format extractors, JSON and PDF extractors. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  Package initialization, symbol re-export, public API surface. \par \b Input\/ \:  None \par \b Output\/ \:  Public symbols: AbstractAttachmentsExtractor, AbstractOfficeAttachmentsExtractor, DocxAttachmentsExtractor, ExcelAttachmentsExtractor, JsonAttachmentsExtractor, PDFAttachmentsExtractor, PptxAttachmentsExtractor \par \b Links\/ \:  [USES_API(9): AbstractAttachmentsExtractor, AbstractOfficeAttachmentsExtractor, DocxAttachmentsExtractor, ExcelAttachmentsExtractor, JsonAttachmentsExtractor, PDFAttachmentsExtractor, PptxAttachmentsExtractor] \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><bold>all</bold> ALWAYS contains all 7 public symbols.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Every concrete extractor listed in <bold>all</bold> is importable from this package. \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why re-export everything here instead of importing from subpackages? A: Single import surface simplifies client code: <computeroutput>from <ref refid="namespacededoc_1_1attachments__extractors" kindref="compound">dedoc.attachments_extractors</ref> import DocxAttachmentsExtractor</computeroutput>. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
<para>LAST_CHANGE: [v1.0.0 – Semantic markup added] \par \b Module Map\/ \:</para>
